    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="386"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d386">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 81.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 16th ultimo,
                    No. 32, which is ac companied by a copy of your note of the 3d of the same month
                    to M. Miguet, the perpetual secretary of the Academy of Moral and Political
                    Sciences, and a translation of his reply of the 11th in relation to the death of
                    the Hon. Edward Everett. Your thoughtfulness in making the communication, and
                    the manner in which it was done, are highly appreciated, as are the sensibility
                    and respect evinced by the academy upon learning that death had stricken from
                    its rolls our distinguished countryman.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
